Steve Sanders (musician) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Sanders_(musician) 0 Steve Sanders (September 17, 1952 – June 10, 1998) was an American musician, singer and songwriter. He was best known as being the replacement for William Lee Golden, the baritone in The Oak Ridge Boys, who had left the group in 1987.
